<TITLE> Negroponte in Iraq to press Iraqi leaders on reforms </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BAGHDAD, June 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US Deputy Secretary of State John Negroponte met Iraqi officials in Baghdad on Tuesday, the latest senior visitor from Washington to press Prime Minister Nuri al-Maliki for progress on political reforms. A US embassy spokesman confirmed that Negroponte was holding closed-door talks, but gave no further details. The visit comes amid rising calls from the US Congress for the Iraqi government to make headway on issues like the sharing of oil revenues and other steps towards reconciliation between the country's Shia majority, Sunnis and Kurds. Thousands of extra US troops have been deployed in the Iraqi capital to counter sectarian violence and help Maliki to press ahead with reform. But many Americans want their troops to start coming home and Congress is demanding results
